The paper discusses neural architecture search, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, given that the paper focuses on evaluating the learning progress of the controller in ENAS, a specific neural architecture search technique, it is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The other sub-categories are also possible, but less likely, as they are more specific to certain aspects of the paper's content.
